# Server Functions & Import Protection

## File naming (critical)

- Files that export `createServerFn` results **must be `*.api.ts`** — they are imported by
  client code via the RPC bridge.
- **Never** use the `*.server.ts` suffix for anything a client module imports. The suffix
  `**/*.server.*` is hard-denied in the client bundle and the build will fail.
- Truly server-only helpers (e.g. `src/lib/server/*`, `src/lib/supabase/server.ts`) may import
  `@tanstack/react-start/server`, but only ever be referenced **inside** `createServerFn` handlers
  so they are tree-shaken out of the client bundle.

## Handler rules

```ts
export const createLine = createServerFn({ method: "POST" })
  .validator((d: unknown) => createLineSchema.parse(d)) // zod on every input
  .handler(async ({ data }) => {
    const { user, repos } = await requireUser();         // auth enforced here
    return repos.lines.create(user.id, data);            // repositories only
  });
```

- Every mutating/reading server function calls `requireUser()` (or `getServerContext()` when public).
- Keep server-only imports (`getRequestUrl`, cookies, etc.) INSIDE the handler body.
- Client mutation variable types use `z.input<typeof schema>`; the handler validator applies transforms.
